SIMPLE: payable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Payable
<hw>Pay"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>payable</ets>. Cf. <er>Pacable</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That
may, can, or should be paid; suitable to be paid; justly due.</def>
<rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thanks are a tribute <qex>payable</qex> by the poorest.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>That may be discharged
or settled by delivery of value.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Matured; now
due.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>payables</ent>⟦br⟧
